   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Earthquake Relief for Children in Shelters</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On April 16, 2016 a 7.8 Earthquake hit the coast of Ecuador.  The large cities of the coast suffered extensive damage and the communities surrounding these cities even more.  Many families were displaced, an estimated number of people in shelter camps is around 22,000 people. People living in these shelters have had their whole disrupted.  Clara Luna hopes to lessen the burden of the children living in these shelters by providing kids programs and activities in the shelters.</narrative>
  </description>
